msIdentifier.repository: Quaker and Special Collections, Rendel Harris

msContents.summary: The first part (of five) of al-Bukhārī's famous collection of Ḥadīth.

author.name: J. Rendel Harris Collection (Quaker & Special Collections, Haverford College)

supportDesc.foliation: Modern foliation in pencil added, upper left recto; catchwords every verso, lower left.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in maghribi in black ink; pointed, vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Illuminated headpiece in red, blue, green (f. 1v); textblock border ruled in double red and blue; rubrications in red, blue, and green.

binding.p: Red leather over pasteboard with flap (Type II); central mandorla stamped onlay with gold-tooled outline and frame.

origin.p: Item is undated, likely copied in the 19th century, based on the paper.
